body:
I know I'm not a known person around League but I just wanted to take some time to thank everyone. Yesterday, I learned that someone hacked my account while I was taking a break from League and used 3rd party applications, resulting in a permanent ban. I submitted a ticket to Riot, but they aren't willing to lift the ban. This still seems surreal to me and I'll definitely miss playing. I know it's just a game but I met a lot of great friends and people through League that I'm extremely grateful for. I really wish I wouldn't have took a break that way I would've known someone hacked my account. Hopefully this will give some of you guys a laugh. Two years ago I was short 8 RP for Mecha Kha'Zix when it came on sale and Riot would grant me the missing RP if I drew something League of Legends related. Farewell everyone. 

